"script": "Deep in the rainforests of Central and South America lives a creature that looks like it's made of glass. The glass frog has skin so translucent on its underside that you can see its beating heart, intestines, and liver. Scientists recently discovered its secret: when it goes to sleep, it hides almost all of its red blood cells inside its liver. This makes the frog up to 60% more transparent, Allowing it to blend in perfectly with the green leaves it rests on. When it wakes up, the blood cells rush back into circulation, And the frog becomes visible again.",
